Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.55,0:00:04.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dying message".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.66,0:00:10.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A pointed message left by a victim of murder in their final moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.54,0:00:13.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Solve the puzzle in that message,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.57,0:00:19.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,900)}and you might be able to force the killer into broad daylight...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.35,0:00:25.09,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Thanks to the years we've spent standing side by side,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.09,0:00:27.42,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}we go onward now without ever skipping a beat!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.42,0:00:31.06,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The strained relationships of TV dramas hold nothing on this relationship!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.06,0:00:32.69,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.69,0:00:34.45,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.45,0:00:36.85,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.93,0:02:25.37,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Beika Shrine"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.41,0:02:44.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.21,0:02:49.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I never meant to kill you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.68,0:02:53.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.36,0:02:55.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.52,0:02:57.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,OK! That's it for this scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.03,0:02:59.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was some fine acting, Yoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.41,0:03:03.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Filming a TV drama is interesting,\Ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.96,0:03:04.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.22,0:03:07.70,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Popular Idol\NYoko Okino (21)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.37,0:03:07.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.43,0:03:14.63,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Leading Man\NShingo Nachi (23)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.35,0:03:14.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As if the great leading man\NShingo Nachi would ever mess up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:17.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! You must be exhausted!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.66,0:03:19.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.54,0:03:22.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What an amazing performance that was!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.37,0:03:23.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm absolutely certain that this drama
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:25.90,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Tuesday Suspense Drama
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:25.90,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Blackmailers Who Scoff\Nin the Darkness"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:25.90,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Shooting Script
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:25.90,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Nichiuri TV
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.79,0:03:25.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,will go down as a masterpiece!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.90,0:03:29.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But only because you helped\Nsupervise the mystery writing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.62,0:03:32.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.09,0:03:34.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have with us the famous\Ndetective who's known
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.28,0:03:35.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as the modern-day Kogoro Akechi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.54,0:03:38.52,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Director\NTaketoshi Gondo (57)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.05,0:03:38.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This drama's going to be a\Nsmash hit, no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.52,0:03:42.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose I did help a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.00,0:03:47.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's on top of the world now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.79,0:03:51.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This goes here, and this goes like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.31,0:03:54.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Way too easy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.07,0:03:54.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.83,0:03:57.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be touching my things!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.96,0:03:59.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.78,0:04:01.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't paying close enough attention to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.30,0:04:06.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess I can forgive him\Nif it's for a cute girl like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.75,0:04:08.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.68,0:04:10.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Bah. What a smooth talker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.48,0:04:13.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're into matchstick puzzles, Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.93,0:04:19.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, leading men like me\Nprefer intelligent hobbies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.56,0:04:22.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.80,0:04:27.36,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Continuity Checker\NTaeko Mamegaki (24)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.99,0:04:26.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Good work today!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.41,0:04:27.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's a towel!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.36,0:04:29.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.35,0:04:33.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, would you have dinner with me tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.00,0:04:34.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.65,0:04:36.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.30,0:04:37.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.45,0:04:41.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She and this kid are getting hitched next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.34,0:04:42.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ain't that right, Shimazaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.44,0:04:46.20,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant Director\NYuji Shimazaki (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.02,0:04:45.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.47,0:04:50.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.33,0:04:51.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.15,0:04:54.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They only seem like flowers\Nbefore you marry them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.37,0:04:57.97,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant Photographer\NMorio Anzai (25)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.51,0:04:57.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know it's an illusion until it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.97,0:04:59.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.77,0:05:02.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Yuji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.11,0:05:04.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He always has something bad to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.53,0:05:06.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get so upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.07,0:05:11.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my watch's alarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.93,0:05:16.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool sound, huh? I bought it last month\Nwhen I went to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.66,0:05:20.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess you don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.87,0:05:23.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See you chumps later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.33,0:05:25.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What a jerk...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.81,0:05:29.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, three...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.71,0:05:32.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are they finished filming?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.33,0:05:33.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.45,0:05:36.58,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko's Grandfather\NKyusaku Mamegaki (75)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.17,0:05:36.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure to clean everything up\Nbefore you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.57,0:05:39.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.10,0:05:41.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We will, Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.71,0:05:43.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I leave it in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.57,0:05:48.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your grandfather is the shrine keeper here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.98,0:05:52.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this shrine is where I grew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.20,0:05:54.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.38,0:05:57.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't your friend ask you\Nto get Shingo Nachi's autograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.29,0:05:59.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.46,0:06:00.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.34,0:06:02.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Already went to change clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.30,0:06:03.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.17,0:06:05.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a sec, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.17,0:06:08.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut the crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.58,0:06:10.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.19,0:06:11.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even have any proof?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.89,0:06:13.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.39,0:06:18.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want these photos and negatives,\Nyou know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.13,0:06:18.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Money?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.76,0:06:22.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.24,0:06:25.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.66,0:06:31.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. We'll be staying at this inn tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.81,0:06:34.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about a nice bath and a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.65,0:06:36.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.28,0:06:38.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.39,0:06:40.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} should come too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.45,0:06:42.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.18,0:06:44.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a crappy-looking inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.45,0:06:47.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A leading man such as me would\Nnever stay in a place like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:51.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This constant talk about being a\Nleading man is really annoying...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.93,0:06:54.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be staying at the Teitan Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.48,0:06:57.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.64,0:06:59.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's hopeless...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.70,0:07:05.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Drink up, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.03,0:07:09.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.16,0:07:11.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Anzai! Where you goin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.16,0:07:13.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The camera doesn't keep\Nitself tuned up, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.53,0:07:16.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What an unfriendly fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.60,0:07:21.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. I need to take care\Nof something at home...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.04,0:07:23.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Hurry back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.12,0:07:33.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need make-up,\NRan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! You're still young!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.25,0:07:35.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's Shimazaki{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.98,0:07:40.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shimazaki! Get me some\Ncigarettes while you're out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.32,0:07:41.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.89,0:07:45.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Let's go to the convenience store!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.55,0:07:50.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it a bad idea for an idol\Nto walk outside at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.01,0:07:52.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.04,0:07:56.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody'll recognize me if I change\Nmy hairstyle and wear a hat!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.60,0:07:57.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I saw them changing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.14,0:08:01.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Are you really sure this is okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.78,0:08:03.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.39,0:08:09.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s going out too...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.00,0:08:15.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You worry too much, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.87,0:08:16.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.21,0:08:18.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.59,0:08:21.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.95,0:08:23.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.26,0:08:24.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.86,0:08:26.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.44,0:08:28.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.05,0:08:33.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.80,0:08:38.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? I told you we'd be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.70,0:08:41.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were right! They didn't recognize you at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:45.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.82,0:08:47.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it was an offering thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.97,0:08:55.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-There's someone on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.13,0:09:00.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.45,0:09:04.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead! Call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.34,0:09:06.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.23,0:09:07.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.92,0:09:16.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Even if the victim's hat fell off when he collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.14,0:09:17.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}how did his vest come off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.06,0:09:24.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is the knife they used during filming!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.34,0:09:29.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Which means that the killer was\Nsomeone on the filming crew!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.66,0:09:38.66,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fu Dog"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.66,0:09:42.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is a dying message the victim left behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.92,0:09:44.64,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Fu Dog?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.64,0:09:47.43,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Is this a clue to who did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.26,0:09:56.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw someone suspicious\Nbefore you found the body, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.31,0:10:00.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. But it was too dark to even tell\Nif it was a man or a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.98,0:10:02.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that was around 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.00,0:10:06.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the murder\Ntook place between 10:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.31,0:10:09.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when the victim left the inn at 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.98,0:10:14.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. This case is surprisingly simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.07,0:10:15.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.33,0:10:21.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First off, the murder weapon\Nwas used during the show's filming.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.55,0:10:24.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Second, "Fu Dog" clearly\Nrefers to the Shinto shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.42,0:10:27.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From these two facts alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.77,0:10:29.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...the killer must be you, Taeko Mamegaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.98,0:10:32.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense! Taeko would never kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.80,0:10:37.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. You were gone for nearly\Nan hour during the party, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.61,0:10:41.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I needed to get something at home...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.18,0:10:43.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our house is behind the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.27,0:10:45.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can anyone verify that you were there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.79,0:10:49.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather was out at the time,\Nso I was the only one there...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.08,0:10:54.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came back\Njust as Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left the inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.70,0:10:56.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.70,0:11:00.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After she came back, she stayed\Nin the hall the whole time...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.02,0:11:04.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means she couldn't possibly have killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.37,0:11:06.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Get a hold of yourself, will ya?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.64,0:11:12.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone among you leave the inn\Nbetween 10:00 and 10:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.34,0:11:17.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... I went to buy cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.04,0:11:19.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When was this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.33,0:11:20.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.15,0:11:21.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,9:45!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.88,0:11:25.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I happened to look at my watch just then!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.12,0:11:26.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And when did you return?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.37,0:11:29.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,About 30 minutes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.07,0:11:31.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which would be 10:15?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.59,0:11:32.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.74,0:11:34.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.45,0:11:38.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you were the only one who decided to stay at the Teitan Hotel instead of this inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.69,0:11:44.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My pride as a leading man wouldn't\Nlet me stay in such a hovel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.52,0:11:48.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you between 10:00 and 10:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.15,0:11:50.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in the hotel bar until 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.84,0:11:52.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plenty of people can vouch for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.53,0:11:53.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking about after that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.84,0:11:56.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in my hotel room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.59,0:11:58.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can anyone verify this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.14,0:12:00.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was by myself, so no!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.04,0:12:04.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The killer's someone on the filming crew...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.12,0:12:08.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Our only clue is the phrase "Fu Dog",\Nwhich the victim wrote...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.13,0:12:11.91,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Taeko{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} is the one most\Nclosely connected to fu dogs...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.91,0:12:17.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But she returned to the inn just\Nas the victim was leaving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.54,0:12:18.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.51,0:12:23.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...why was she so surprised then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.38,0:12:27.51,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shimazaki{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} went to buy cigarettes at 9:45
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.51,0:12:29.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and returned to the inn at 10:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.66,0:12:31.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}More than enough time to commit the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.25,0:12:35.84,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But it was 10:30 when we\Nsaw the person at the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.84,0:12:38.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shimazaki{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was back at the inn by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.19,0:12:42.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Nachi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} has no alibi after 10:00—\Nhe could have done it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.11,0:12:45.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It sounded like he was being\Nblackmailed by the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.28,0:12:47.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so in terms of motive, he's the most suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.22,0:12:52.08,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And Nachi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was most likely\Nthe one we saw in the shadows!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.80,0:12:55.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! We found these in the victim's room!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.35,0:13:02.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... This is you\Nleaving a hotel with a woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.67,0:13:06.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the actress Ritsuko Hagiyama!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.56,0:13:09.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But she's married!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.41,0:13:12.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Photographic evidence of your infidelity...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.28,0:13:14.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.90,0:13:19.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} trying to\Nblackmail Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.48,0:13:21.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Blackmail?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.89,0:13:23.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you are the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.94,0:13:26.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you, I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.01,0:13:29.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If I killed him, then what the\Nhell does "Fu Dog" mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.30,0:13:31.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure that's not one of your nicknames?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.54,0:13:32.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.51,0:13:36.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What exactly does this "Fu Dog" mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.73,0:13:40.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.82,0:13:42.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why would he go through the\Ntrouble of writing it down?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.27,0:13:45.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He was killed right in front of a fu dog—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.24,0:13:47.08,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}all he had to do was point at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.08,0:13:49.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There was no need to write it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.51,0:13:52.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.71,0:14:00.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even have any proof that I was here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.10,0:14:01.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? This writing is weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.35,0:14:04.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This character isn't drawn right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.61,0:14:05.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That lousy kid's at it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.62,0:14:08.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times do I have to—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.70,0:14:13.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This man was an adult, but he\Ncouldn't even write katakana right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.01,0:14:17.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're supposed to write this part here all in one stroke.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.05,0:14:19.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he wrote it using two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.76,0:14:21.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.11,0:14:24.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.30,0:14:27.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He did the same with the last character too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.81,0:14:28.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.20,0:14:35.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if these incorrect strokes were\Nactually lines that were added later?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.01,0:14:38.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Leading man"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.68,0:14:41.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only leading man\Naround here is Shingo Nachi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.25,0:14:44.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like some definitive\Nproof has shown itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.45,0:14:47.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.44,0:14:51.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll admit that I was supposed\Nto meet Anzai here at 10:30,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.59,0:14:54.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but when I showed up, he was already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.29,0:14:56.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of this tomfoolery!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.87,0:15:00.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth! He really was dead when I got here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.19,0:15:03.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was about to run away, but then\NI saw "leading man" written there...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.81,0:15:07.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I added some vertical lines like\Nin the matchstick puzzles that I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.74,0:15:12.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're not the killer, then why\Ndid the victim write "leading man"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.65,0:15:13.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell if I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.98,0:15:15.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.48,0:15:18.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's not normal for someone\Nto fake a dying message
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.06,0:15:20.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}but not come up with a fake alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.68,0:15:24.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Maybe the real killer altered the\Nmessage to say "leading man"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.82,0:15:32.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could this be what I think it is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.55,0:15:36.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It {\i1}couldn't{\i0} have been that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.18,0:15:39.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.38,0:15:44.67,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's no blood on this watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.67,0:15:47.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Aha! That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.85,0:15:50.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now I know the truth behind this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.94,0:15:52.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me! I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.93,0:15:56.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to how pathetic you sound,\NMr. Leading Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.26,0:16:05.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can give us the details down at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.23,0:16:06.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.70,0:16:11.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure. Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is not the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.20,0:16:12.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.60,0:16:17.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason being that the\Nmurder took place before 10:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.04,0:16:19.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.00,0:16:20.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.68,0:16:24.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} leave the inn around 10:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.25,0:16:26.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We even heard his watch alarm go off!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.63,0:16:30.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. Have a look at the victim's wristwatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.10,0:16:31.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.75,0:16:36.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His entire left arm is covered in blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.47,0:16:39.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's none at all on his watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.08,0:16:40.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.48,0:16:45.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, someone\Nremoved the watch from the body
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.23,0:16:47.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after the victim was killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.44,0:16:50.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone removed his watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.34,0:16:55.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This particular person wanted to make it look like the murder happened later than it actually did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.42,0:16:58.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer came up with the idea\Nof taking the watch back to the inn
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.44,0:17:01.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and setting the alarm off in the victim's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.85,0:17:05.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it would cause problems if\Nblood dripped off it on the way back,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.25,0:17:07.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the killer wiped the watch clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.67,0:17:10.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the person we saw at the inn was—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.03,0:17:13.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. That wasn't Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.66,0:17:17.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who set the\Nalarm off in Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.33,0:17:22.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,put his vest and hat on and left the\Ninn disguised as Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.51,0:17:26.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This person rushed back to the shrine,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.82,0:17:29.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,put the watch back on the dead body,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.45,0:17:32.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then dropped the hat and vest nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.57,0:17:37.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the killer wrote "leading man"\Nto make Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} look guilty!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.94,0:17:39.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the killer wanted Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to look guilty,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.75,0:17:41.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,why not just write "Nachi"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.85,0:17:44.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That would have been a much\Nmore effective way of fooling us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.75,0:17:47.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer couldn't write "Nachi".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.07,0:17:50.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason being that the victim\Nhad already written something
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.68,0:17:52.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that identified the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.17,0:17:53.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something that identified the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.68,0:17:55.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.02,0:17:57.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Leading man" was actually a\Nsingle word that the victim wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.92,0:18:00.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with extra strokes added in later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.45,0:18:04.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what was the original\Nword the victim wrote?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.05,0:18:07.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was "Mame".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.29,0:18:12.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko Mamegaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. You're the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.03,0:18:14.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense! She would never!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.75,0:18:16.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:17.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.95,0:18:23.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} returned to the inn just as\Nthe person disguised as Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.90,0:18:26.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was me! I killed Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.95,0:18:28.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who dressed up as him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.36,0:18:31.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the word "Mame" wasn't written there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.12,0:18:35.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shimazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. You were indeed\Nthe one who dressed up as him,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.47,0:18:37.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but you cannot possibly be the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.08,0:18:41.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See the huge spray of blood around the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.18,0:18:44.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer must have been\Ncovered in a lot of blood as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.13,0:18:47.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's not even a single drop on your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.52,0:18:52.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only person who had time to\Nchange clothes and wash off the blood
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.78,0:18:54.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.60,0:18:57.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.87,0:19:00.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.26,0:19:00.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.75,0:19:04.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just as you said, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.07,0:19:06.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.01,0:19:07.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.39,0:19:08.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.25,0:19:14.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I take it you didn't know\NShimazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had dressed up as him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.07,0:19:15.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.14,0:19:21.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I was really shocked when\NI saw Anzai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} at the front door...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.02,0:19:23.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea what was going on anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.77,0:19:25.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why, Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.06,0:19:31.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Anzai was\Nblackmailing you too, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.58,0:19:33.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.82,0:19:37.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was in high school,\NI turned rebellious for a short time
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.46,0:19:39.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after my parents died in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.26,0:19:44.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I stopped going to school and started\Nhanging out with the wrong crowd...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.19,0:19:47.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzai was one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.73,0:19:50.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.24,0:19:52.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember when everyone was in an uproar
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.02,0:19:55.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after that expensive statue was\Nstolen from the shrine storehouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.87,0:19:57.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.27,0:20:00.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.85,0:20:05.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After I mentioned it to Anzai,\Nhe immediately went and stole it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.73,0:20:07.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.55,0:20:09.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.43,0:20:12.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.50,0:20:15.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Sugiyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was\Nin charge of the storehouse,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.36,0:20:18.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,felt responsible for it and killed himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.05,0:20:22.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was too scared to say anything after seeing that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.82,0:20:25.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I quit hanging\Naround Anzai and the others,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.97,0:20:28.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I started taking school seriously again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.56,0:20:33.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had nearly managed to suppress\Nthe memories of that detestable event!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.21,0:20:38.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All I wanted was to marry\NYuji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and start a happy family!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.02,0:20:40.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then he showed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.05,0:20:42.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he tried to blackmail you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.75,0:20:44.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.18,0:20:46.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said that since I had been an accomplice,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.67,0:20:50.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just as responsible\Nfor Sugiyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.00,0:20:51.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me over and over!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.73,0:20:57.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt that if something wasn't done,\Nhe would ruin our marriage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.06,0:21:02.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was supposed to pay Anzai\Nsome money here at 9:30 tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.24,0:21:07.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But instead, I brought a knife\Nand threatened Anzai back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.62,0:21:10.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told him never to show\Nhis face around me ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.94,0:21:13.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He got mad and rushed for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.83,0:21:16.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...and then the knife just happened to—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.68,0:21:25.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I never meant to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.56,0:21:33.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You seemed strange when you left,\Nso I pretended to go buy cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.28,0:21:37.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I got to the shrine, Anzai was dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.00,0:21:39.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the word "Mame" was written in blood next to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.87,0:21:42.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured you were the one who killed him,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.58,0:21:45.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I tried my hardest to alter all the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.08,0:21:46.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wiped the fingerprints off the knife,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.62,0:21:49.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and took Anzai's watch back to the inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.61,0:21:52.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest is exactly as Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} deduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.19,0:21:55.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I should've just gotten rid of that writing in blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.06,0:21:58.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then I remembered how he\Nthreatened Nachi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} earlier this evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.39,0:22:02.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I made "Mame" say "leading man" instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.34,0:22:06.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry, Yuji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.09,0:22:07.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taeko!
